for 400g pork belly (/spare rib strips)
- blanch pork belly cubes for a few mins & drain
- add veg oil and 20g sugar to a 160°C pan to melt and start caramelising (few mins)
- add chopped onion and cook for a few mins until translucent
- add pork
- add 1/4 cup dark soy
- 1/4 cup light soy
- 1/4 cup shaoxing
- top up with water
- cover with lid and simmer for 1.5 hours, stirring every 15 mins to prevent burning
- remove lid and cook down to thicken sauce

jap variant:
- replace shaoxing with sake
- add 1/8 cup mirin
- drop soys to 1/8 cup
- a teaspoon/tbsp of miso?
